In the government of Britain the representatives of the people compose one branch of the national legislature.,0,0,0,0,0,0
Commerce has been for ages the predominant pursuit of that country.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"Few nations, nevertheless, have been more frequently engaged in war; and the wars in which that kingdom has been engaged have, in numerous instances, proceeded from the people.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"There have been, if I may so express it, almost as many popular as royal wars.",0,0,0,0,0,0
