"In reading many of the publications against the Constitution, a man is apt to imagine that he is perusing some ill-written tale or romance, which instead of natural and agreeable images, exhibits to the mind nothing but frightful and distorted shapes--                 Gorgons, hydras, and chimeras dire; discoloring and disfiguring whatever it represents, and transforming everything it touches into a monster.",1,0,0,0,0,0
